article.headline: Murray State 92, Tennessee Tech 75
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- Chris Shumate scored 17 points, leading six players in double figures as Murray State beat Tennessee Tech 92-75 in the first round of the Ohio Valley Conference tournament Tuesday night. Antione Whelchel added 15 for Murray (26-5), Cuthbert Victor had 13, Kelvin Brown and Andi Hornig 12 each and Kevin Paschel 10. Cameron Crisp scored 30 points for the Golden Eagles (13-15) on 11-of-22 shooting from the field and an 8-of-13 performance from 3-point range. Murray State led 43-36 at halftime and ran out the lead to 20 points with 12:46 remaining when Brown hit two free throws. Tennessee Tech cut the lead to nine with 5:48 left in the game on a free throw by Keyon Boyd. During that run, the Golden Eagles made five 3-pointers, four by Crisp and one by Willie Jenkins, who finished with 21 points on the night. Will Moore scored 10 for Tech. Murray advances to play Morehead State in the semifinals Friday in Nashville, Tenn.
